        "author_role": "REVIEWER",
        "timestamp": "2018-06-28 23:31:37.000000000",
        "message": "Patch Set 1:\n\nFolks, this change does not seem right to me, I think it should be reverted.   What is trying to fix is basic functionality that has worked since amsterdam release, otherwise, healthhcheck, the use cases, and other functionality would have not worked, and that has been tested out working hundreds of times by different teams in both amsterdam and beijing.   The corresponding do-start.sh will do this work in the heat and oom installations.   This could have potentially unknown sideffects, and will be executed multiple times.   It also does not constrain it to be executed for only the pap component.  I don't think this is the right fix, if there's is a real coding problem which I also question.",
        "patchset_number": 1
      },
